cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of lesion segmentation in dermoscopy images. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and the exploration of more robust and precise models also suggest the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on skin lesion analysis and melanoma detection indicates the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, while the use of dilation convolution and conditional random field methods suggests the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
